description:
&lt;p&gt;A new opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, highly organised and motivated individual to join our busy Procurement team at Mid Cheshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust presently based at Leighton Hospital in Crewe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be part of a dedicated team playing their part in delivering an efficient and cost effective supplies service to our organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Procurement Officer will proactively manage the transactional buying team and will be an important link between the team and the senior team. It is expected that the Procurement Officer will, under the general guidance of the Senior Procurement Officer, manage day to day activities of the team including, but not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of performance metrics and management of team performance;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management and delegation of workloads. This includes monitoring activity as required and ensuring that work is distributed in a fair and equitable manner;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Line management of the transactional buying team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on specified ‘mid-range’ (i.e. medium value, medium to high complexity) procurement projects. The Procurement Officer shall use a range of tools and techniques to devise appropriate procurement solutions, utilizing a working and legal knowledge of contracting and ensure contracts are awarded in accordance with Trust and public procurement processes;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct procurement and commercial analysis in support of procurement projects and verify financial information from suppliers and generate written reports to support decisions/contract award recommendations;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be able to demonstrate that they have managed a team and introduced change in a fast paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is being advertised on the basis of 37.5 W.T.E hours per week Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an Informal discussion and for further information, in the first instance please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Geoff Edwards - geoffrey.edwards@mcht.nhs.uk or call 07971 618397&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ed Gough - edwin.gough@mcht.nhs.uk or call 07971 618342&lt;/p&gt;
